subSubSection.paragraph:
Ph. spumarius
is a polyphagous species with a very wide range of hosts and the preference to nitrogen fixing plants (
Thompson 1994
;
Owen 1988
) and can be found on large numbers of dicotyledonous plant species (
Drosopoulos 2003
). It is considered as a pest on alfalfa and strawberry and a potential vector for the bacterium
X. fastidiosa
which infests olive trees (
Peck & Thompson 2008
;
European Food Safety Authority 2013
), a resource of Pierce’s disease virus, the vector of elm yellows phytoplasma (
Rosa et al ., 2014
,
DeLong & Severin 1950
). The mentioned published data shows the activity of this species in the elevation of 1350m to 3900m in Iran . However, our examined material indicates the presence of the species at a minimum of 900m elevation.
